  "description": "The Short Nutritional Assessment Questionnaire (SNAQ) is a (validated) measuring tool for determining the extent of a patientâ€™s malnutrition. The tool comprises three questions, each of which is assigned a score. The total score determines the extent of malnutrition.\r\nThe SNAQ helps to recognize and treat malnutrition at an early stage.\r\nThree varieties of the measuring tool were developed for different care settings: hospitals, nursing and retirement homes and independently living seniors. This concept describes the tool intended for the hospital setting.",
